<Content>A great L.A. experience I just got back from the Sofitel where I had a girlfriend weekend getaway. It was a great experience. We stayed in a suite and were on the penthouse floor. The only complaint was the sound of sirens that occasionally went by enroute to Cedars Sinai hospital which was a block away from the hotel. The staff were all very courteous with the exception of one concierge who seemed to be a gal with a poor attitude and work ethic. The other concierge staff were amazing getting us a reservation at Madeo restaurant with only a couple hours notice. The dining at the hotel was pretty decent food and the breakfast fare was quite reasonably priced as well. The room was very clean and always replenished with complimentary Evian bottles of water. The pool was a great little spot with TV's in some of the cabanas and music playing. Room service would also come and bring you drinks and food if requested at the pool. The location of the hotel was fabulous. It is directly across the street from a pretty standard mall. It was within walking distance to some really fine dining - Madeo, The Jar, The Ivy. It is very close to walk to the Farmer's Market, CBS Studios and The Grove outdoor shopping center (great spot). It is a short 3 block walk to Robertson Boulevard which has some fabulous shopping. Melrose Avenue is a hike but we walked to it (disappointing as it is really rundown and the type of shopping where you have to really be in the mood to find what you are looking for).We didn't really frequent the Stone Rose Lounge except for a pre-dinner drink but it seemed to have a really great vibe.My friend and I have decided that we will definitely be back to L.A. for our girl's weekend and enjoyed it better than our last Vegas trip at the Bellagio. We will definitely be back to the Sofitel on our next trip. 
