<Author>eclecticone
<Content>I heart Sofitel The Sofitel leaves not one detail spared. We stayed in a King Superior room for $220/night. After shopping many, many LA/BH hotels, I found this to be very reasonable. After you stay one night at Sofitel you won't regret one penny spent. The room is decorated with whites and browns for a very modern and clean appearance. The shower was unbelievable with a fog window so you can watch TV (42 HD LCD with surround sound in bathroom) while showering if you wish. The hotel supplies each bathroom with fine soaps and shampoo (which I enjoy as I travel a ton).The customer service was excellent. We never felt out of place at this swanky hotel. There is someone to help you with everything (luggage, valet, housekeeping), so come prepared with plenty of $1 bills. The parking is $26/night which is comparable to other LA hotels but is an added expense that must be considered.The pool and fitness center were excellent. Luckily, the pool wasn't crowded so it was quiet and relaxing. The pool chairs are super comfortable.The fitness is state of the art with some of the best equipment available. They also offered free bottles of water and cool scented towels.We will stay at Sofitel in the future whenever possible. 
